ENTRY       EC 3.2.1.175                Enzyme
NAME        beta-D-glucopyranosyl abscisate beta-glucosidase;
            AtBG1;
            ABA-beta-D-glucosidase;
            ABA-specific beta-glucosidase;
            ABA-GE hydrolase;
            beta-D-glucopyranosyl abscisate hydrolase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Glycosylases;
            Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
SYSNAME     beta-D-glucopyranosyl abscisate glucohydrolase
REACTION    D-glucopyranosyl abscisate + H2O = D-glucose + abscisate [RN:R09723]
ALL_REAC    R09723
SUBSTRATE   D-glucopyranosyl abscisate;
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     D-glucose [CPD:C00031];
            abscisate [CPD:C06082]
COMMENT     The enzyme hydrolzes the biologically inactive beta-D-glucopyranosyl ester of abscisic acid to produce active abscisate. Abscisate is a phytohormone critical for plant growth, development and adaption to various stress conditions. The enzyme does not hydrolyse beta-D-glucopyranosyl zeatin [1].
